That part — the part about pitching — is the one element of his life that seems to make sense right now.
“It’s like the twilight zone,” Sampson says from his high-rise apartment in Busan, home of the Lotte Giants.
I think the KBO is setting a really good example for what should be done.”In the meantime, Sampson just keeps living day by day.
He had been looking forward to exploring Korean culture as he’s got a little bit of wanderlust.
He’s already endured a life’s worth of them in four months.